Reasoning: The paper focuses on multi-agent reinforcement learning in the context of load balancing in a distributed system, which falls under the category of multi-agent systems (cs.MA). The paper also discusses the stochastic nature of the system and the purely local information available to individual agents, which are important features of distributed computing (cs.DC) and distributed systems (cs.DS). The paper also explores the interplay between basic adaptive behavior parameters and their effect on system efficiency, which is a topic in machine learning (cs.LG) and control systems (cs.SY).
